# üü¢ 4-Channel Relay Board with Opto-Isolation for Arduino/Raspberry Pi

This project is a **modular, 4-channel relay control board** designed for microcontrollers like **Arduino, Raspberry Pi, ESP32, etc.
** The board features **opto-isolation** for electrical protection and safety, and is ideal for **home automation**, **IoT**, or **industrial control** applications.

---

## üì¶ Features

- ‚úÖ **4 independent relays** (SPDT type) ‚Äì control AC/DC loads up to 250V AC / 30V DC
- ‚úÖ **4 opto-isolated inputs** ‚Äì control each relay with 3.3V or 5V logic
- ‚úÖ **Load-side isolation** ‚Äì added safety through PCB cutouts (drilled part under relay contacts)
- ‚úÖ **Status indicator LEDs** ‚Äì per-relay operation feedback
- ‚úÖ Designed for **Arduino, Raspberry Pi, ESP8266, ESP32**, etc.
- ‚úÖ Screw terminals for easy wiring of relays and power

---

## ‚öôÔ∏è Technical Specs

| Component            | Description                     |
|----------------------|---------------------------------|
| **Relay type**       | 5V or 12V SPDT (choose model)   |
| **Optocoupler**      | PC817 or equivalent             |
| **Input voltage**    | 5V logic compatible             |
| **Isolation**        | Optical + PCB drilled spacing   |
| **Max switching**    | 10A 250V AC / 10A 30V DC        |
| **Board size**       | 65mmx70mm                |
| **Control headers**  | 4-pin input control (IN1‚ÄìIN4)   |
| **Load terminals**   | NO, COM, NC per relay           |

---

## üìå Pinout

| Pin | Description           |
|-----|-----------------------|
| IN1 | Control for Relay 1   |
| IN2 | Control for Relay 2   |
| IN3 | Control for Relay 3   |
| IN4 | Control for Relay 4   |
| VCC | Input side power (5V) |
| GND | Ground                |

Each control input drives one relay via an optocoupler for full isolation.

